OL,3,CUK urged to rein in spending as debt
OL,4,Cspirals beyond other developed
OL,5,Ceconomies
OL,7,F"The global battle against inflation
OL,8,Fhas largely been won," Pierre-Olivier
OL,9,FGourinchas, the IMF's Economic
OL,10,FController in World Economic Outlook,
OL,11,Fsaid.
OL,13,FPrices are stabilising and the IMF
OL,14,Fwants central banks and governments to
OL,15,Frespond accordingly. The former is by
OL,16,Fcutting interest rates. The latter, by
OL,17,F"urgently" sorting out their balance
OL,18,Fsheets.
