OL,3,CUK urged to rein in spending as debt
OL,4,Cspirals beyond other developed
OL,5,Ceconomies
OL,7,FThese nations borrowed heavily in
OL,8,Forder to support businesses and
OL,9,Fhouseholds during the pandemic and the
OL,10,Fenergy shock - they now find
OL,11,Fthemselves in a precarious position.
OL,13,FGaurinchas said a lack of political
OL,14,Fwill, in parts of the world, to face
OL,15,Fthis challenge head-on, but insists
OL,16,Ffailure to act runs the risk of
OL,17,F"disorderly market imposed
OL,18,Fadjustments," similar to the sort Liz
OL,19,FTruss triggered.
