OL,3,CUK urged to rein in spending as debt
OL,4,Cspirals beyond other developed
OL,5,Ceconomies
OL,7,F"Success," Gourinchas added, requires
OL,8,F"implementing gradual and credible
OL,9,Fmultiyear adjustments without delay"
OL,10,Fwhile adding that aggressive tax rises
OL,11,For spending cuts would be "self-
OL,12,Fdefeating".
OL,14,FThe IMF's figures show that the ratio
OL,15,Fbetween government debt and gross
OL,16,Fdomestic product (GDP) - an important
OL,17,Findicator of a country's economic
OL,18,Fhealth - has risen by 57 percentage
OL,19,Fpoints in the UK in the last 20 years.
