OL,7,FThe following month, on a visit to the
OL,8,FUK, the IMF said the government's
OL,9,Fspending plans beyond April 2025 are
OL,10,Funrealistically low and that whoever
OL,11,Fwon the election would need to either
OL,12,Fraise taxes by between #22 billion and
OL,13,F#39 billion a year or find equivalent
OL,14,Fsavings to get debt under control.
OL,16,FAdding that whoever won the election
OL,17,Fwould probably need either to raise
OL,18,F#30 billion a year more by raising
OL,19,Ftaxes or spending would need to be
OL,20,Freduced by a similar amount.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/15
